00:00:18.266 --> 00:00:22.266
PhotoModeler Scanner has four stages to create the final textured 
model. 

00:00:22.266 --> 00:00:25.199
These 3D views show the project after each of these stages.

00:00:25.200 --> 00:00:28.933
This 3D view shows the results of the first stage.  

00:00:28.933 --> 00:00:35.399
The SmartMatch process matches key features across the 
photos and uses these to solve the camera positions as well as 
creating this sparse point set.

00:00:35.400 --> 00:00:41.500
The solution from the first stage is used by the multi-view stereo 
system - M V S for short ...

00:00:41.500 --> 00:00:46.233
...to create this dense point cloud.  Zooming in you can see the 
points created by this step.

00:00:46.233 --> 00:00:52.999
Each point in the cloud has it's color extracted from the photos.

00:00:53.000 --> 00:01:02.333
These points are then triangulated during the modify mesh step 
to create this shaded mesh.

00:01:12.666 --> 00:01:16.666
Finally, the triangulated mesh has textures applied from the 
original photos.

00:01:21.233 --> 00:01:25.233
