remaining steps.

00:02:13.666 --> 00:02:25.999
All four steps can be run independently, or they can be run 
together by pressing the Options button, and then selecting 'Run 
DSM'.

00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:30.000
Hit 'Run' and the SmartMatch process starts.

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:34.566
Features are detected on each image and then matched across 
images.  

00:02:34.566 --> 00:02:38.266
 Once the matches are complete the project is then processed.

00:02:38.266 --> 00:02:42.899
While that processes we can review some basic requirements of 
SmartMatch projects.

00:02:42.900 --> 00:02:47.533
A SmartMatch project requires a set of low angle photos with 
good overlap.

00:02:47.533 --> 00:02:52.766
Aim for at least 60% overlap, for example photo 1 should overlap  
photo 2, and some of photo 3.

00:02:52.766 --> 00:02:59.999
The subject matter and/or background should contain random 
features. For example, a feature-less, plain white wall will not 
work. 

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.300
As well, the majority of the scene should not move between 
photos.  

00:03:04.300 --> 00:03:08.033
Avoid using blurry or out of focus photos.

00:03:08.033 --> 00:03:11.733
After the SmartMatch process has solved the camera positions, 
the MVS steps will run.

00:03:11.733 --> 00:03:17.899
By default, MVS requires each part of the object to be visible in a 
minimum of three photos.

00:03:17.900 --> 00:03:26.033
The following subject matter is not suited to the SmartMatch and 
MVS process: Non-textured solid colors,  moving objects, 
reflective objects, ...

00:03:26.033 --> 00:03:29.866
.. and thin objects that cause occlusions.

00:03:29.866 --> 00:03:34.666
After the dense point cloud has been created by MVS, the point 
cloud will be triangulated and cleaned.

